# English-only operator surface

WorldBase is an English-first open-source project. Everything that lives in the repo must be in **English**, including:

- User-visible UI strings (labels, tooltips, errors, buttons, panel titles)
- Briefing prompt section labels: LOCAL / REGION / GLOBAL / RECOMMENDATION
- Default env values in `.env.example` (`WORLDBASE_BRIEFING_LANG=en`)
- Commit messages and PR descriptions
- Code comments, docstrings, log messages
- Cursor assets: `.cursor/skills/**/SKILL.md`, `.cursor/rules/**/*.mdc`, `.cursor/hooks/**/*`
- Root-level docs: `README.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `docs/**/*`

**Exceptions**

- `WORLDBASE_BRIEFING_LANG=de` may produce German briefing output at runtime via `operator_briefing.py` (env-controlled, not source code)
- `LLM_HANDOFF.md` may stay bilingual — historical operator notes for local use only
- Chat between agent and maintainer can be German (per user-level rule); only the artifacts written to disk must be English

When adding strings, match existing HUD style: short uppercase labels, plain tooltips.
